text: I went to the #BlackLivesMatter rally in @CityofFairfaxVA earlier today to listen. What I heard was anguish, frustration, and anger. And, for 8 minutes and 46 seconds, I heard silence, punctuated only by passing cars, chirping birds, and muffled tears.
tweet_text: I went to the #BlackLivesMatter rally in @CityofFairfaxVA earlier today to listen. What I heard was anguish, frustration, and anger. And, for 8 minutes and 46 seconds, I heard silence, punctuated only by passing cars, chirping birds, and muffled tears.

text: But I also heard hope. Hope in the voices of the young people that organized today’s #BlackLivesMatter that previous generations have failed to enact. Hope that the past week will not have been in vain.
